# [MISER=8] Build 5 Live Business Data Visualization Blocks

Build 5 new `viz-` prefixed EDS blocks. All use real Three.js or Canvas rendering,
all pull live data from a URL at page-load (with graceful inline fallback), all look
exceptional and business-realistic. Authoring via Universal Editor — one URL field,
one optional inline fallback field, cosmetic controls. Blocks live at `blocks/viz-<name>/`.
Do NOT overwrite any existing block.

Data loading strategy (shared across all blocks):
- `dataUrl` field → fetch JSON/CSV at page render time (no server-side proxy needed)
- `inlineData` field → CSV/JSON fallback shown if fetch fails or field is empty
- Author sets one or both; block prefers live URL, falls back to inline
- No auth tokens in fields — public endpoints or CORS-enabled APIs only
- For real-time blocks: author sets a WebSocket or SSE URL; block connects client-side

