## Block 2: `viz-pipeline`

**Concept:** Animated SVG/Canvas logistics or data pipeline diagram. Nodes are stages
(Ingest → Process → Validate → Publish → Archive). Animated particles flow along edges
showing throughput. Live counts update from a polling URL. Perfect for an Operations or
Platform Engineering page — shows your actual data infra moving.

**Data format (JSON from URL, polled every 10s):**
```json
{"nodes":[{"id":"ingest","label":"Ingest","count":1420,"status":"healthy"},...],
 "edges":[{"from":"ingest","to":"process","rate":980},...]}
```
Inline fallback: 6-node "Content Supply Chain" pipeline with realistic Adobe-style counts.

**Rendering:**
- Nodes: rounded rectangles with status color ring (green/amber/red) + live counter
- Edges: bezier curves with animated dashed particles (Canvas RAF)
- Particle speed proportional to `rate` — bottlenecks visible at a glance
- Click node → expands to show error rate, p99 latency, last-updated timestamp
- Layout: left-to-right DAG, positions auto-calculated from edge topology

**Fields:** `dataUrl` (text), `pollInterval` (text, default 10s), `inlineData` (text-area), `height` (text)

