## Block 5: `viz-supply-chain`

**Concept:** Animated world map (Three.js PlaneGeometry + public domain map texture or
pure Canvas Mercator projection) showing factories → distribution centers → markets.
Curved animated routes show goods in transit; hover shows shipment details.
Designed for an Operations, Sustainability, or Investor Relations page.

**Data format (JSON from URL):**
```json
{"nodes":[{"id":"factory-sg","label":"Singapore Factory","type":"factory",
           "lat":1.35,"lon":103.82,"output":4200},...],
 "routes":[{"from":"factory-sg","to":"dc-la","volume":840,"eta":"2d","status":"on-time"},...]}
```
Inline fallback: 12-node global chain (Asia factories → US/EU DCs → retail markets)
modeled on a realistic electronics supply chain.

**Rendering:**
- Flat world map on THREE.PlaneGeometry with a CC0 map texture
- Node icons by type rendered as canvas sprites: factory ⚙, DC 🏭, market 🏪
- Routes: animated dashed THREE.CatmullRomCurve3 arcs, color by status
  (green=on-time, amber=delayed, red=disrupted)
- Animated "shipment" dots travel each route at speed proportional to volume
- Side panel: total shipments in transit, on-time %, disruption alerts

**Fields:** `dataUrl` (text), `inlineData` (text-area), `height` (text),
`showLabels` (select: always/hover/never)

