## File layout per block

```
blocks/viz-<name>/
  viz-<name>.js      # decorate(block) — fetch helper + rendering scene
  viz-<name>.css     # layout, dark theme base, panel styles
  _viz-<name>.json   # XWalk model (definitions + models + filters: [])
```

## Shared data-fetch pattern (inline per block, no separate module)

Each block includes a ~15-line `async function fetchData(url, fallback)`:
1. If `url` is empty → return parsed `fallback`
2. `fetch(url, { signal: AbortSignal.timeout(5000) })` → parse JSON or CSV
3. On any error → `console.warn(...)` + return parsed `fallback`

No shared module — self-contained per EDS block convention.

## AEM model constraints

- Max 4 fields per `models[]` entry (xwalk lint rule — split into sub-models if needed)
- All `_viz-*.json`: `definitions` + `models` + `filters: []`
- Add all 5 block IDs to `models/_section.json` filters after creation
- Run `npm run build:json` after touching any model JSON
- Run `npm run lint:fix` after writing JS; must have 0 errors before job completes

